{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fee2a6a5-91d4-4bff-b1ce-a14fbd43a001","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- Remove this line (or set to false): -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.8+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is the only required change.\n2. **Run tests with:** `dotnet test` still works, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it now produces an executable.\n3. **CLI differences:** Some VSTest CLI args (e.g., `--filter`) are replaced by `--filter` with a slightly different syntax under the new platform. Check `dotnet test --help` for updated options.\n4. **Extensions:** If you used VSTest adapters/loggers, replace them with their Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX output).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"767d40fd-07ca-4730-9c27-dee4661d5c23","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"BD04:164F8C:1D8BC7F:212E8A9:6A07C4D2"},"id":"557b0bc1-49d2-4974-9076-0adebe2f3e84","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:01.929Z","parentId":"d05f6027-a3ce-4bd5-bbee-bf22aa6c449b"}
